{
  "texts": [
    "6LSTM Model For our LSTM model we choose a vanilla LSTM and do not analyze more recent variations developed after 2018 (e.g., Melis et al. [2019] and Beck et al.",
    "We also exclude more-recent variations of LSTMs such as GRUs.",
    "Greff et al. [2016] finds that these variants do not improve on the standard LSTM.",
    "We develop a setup based on state-of-the-art LSTMs before the invention of the Transformer using hyperparameters from Melis et al. [2017].",
    "We focus our efforts on a 1-layer LSTM, which seems to perform the best in practice for an LSTM with 10M parameters [Melis et al., 2017]."
  ]
}